Reasoning: The paper deals with lossy compression algorithms, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of random codebooks and databases suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and database systems (cs.DB). The comparison of different algorithms and their performance evaluation falls under the sub-category of Data Compression (cs.DC). The use of hybrid algorithms and the trade-off between compression and complexity may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
